Correspondence School
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a state-funded institution providing education by mail and other media to children living in remote parts of the country or otherwise unable to attend ordinary schools.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:also TCS abbreviation
Pronunciation:
Notes: also as Correspondence elliptical q.v.
